This paper is about style transfer in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses adversarial networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG), and proposes novel evaluation metrics, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions computer vision (cs.CV) as a domain where style transfer has made significant progress, indicating that the authors are familiar with this field and may have drawn inspiration from it.
